IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE ORGANIZATION IS A MANAGING GENERAL PARTNER OF A PARTNERSHIP WHOSE MISSIONS IS TO PROVIDE QUALITY, SAFE AND AFFORDABLE HOUSING FOR LOW INCOME FAMILIES.
IRS990.MissionDescription: IT IS THE MISSION OF MIDPEN HOUSING CORPORATION AND ITS AFFILIATES TO PROVIDE SAFE, AFFORDABLE SHELTER OF HIGH QUALITY TO THOSE IN NEED OF IT; TO HELP ESTABLISH OPPORTUNITY AND STABILITY IN THE LIVES OF ITS RESIDENTS; AND TO FOSTER COMMUNITIES THAT ALLOW PEOPLE FROM ALL ETHNIC, SOCIAL AND ECONOMIC BACKGROUNDS TO LIVE IN DIGNITY, HARMONY AND MUTUAL RESPECT.
IRS990.Description: The corporation is the general partner of a partnership which owns and operates an affordable housing complex.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 IS REVEIWED BY THE CONTROLLER AND THE CFO.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization routinely examine if board members and key employees should recuse based upon a potential conflict and when in doubt the organization errs on the conservative side and members recuse. By renewing our Conflicts statements annually, board members and key employees are routinely reminded to examine their roles in the various avenues of their lives so that they remain keenly aware of possible conflicts.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: No written process available. Board members and compensation committee review using comparable data from compensation study, form 990 of other organizations and then approve.
